<div id="review_2400514188" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2400514188" />
    <a title="My Bookish Delights" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2520645-my-bookish-delights"><img alt="My Bookish Delights" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594482363p2/2520645.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2400514188?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="My Bookish Delights" class="user" itemprop="url" name="My Bookish Delights" href="/user/show/2520645-my-bookish-delights">My Bookish Delights</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/40010645-the-forgotten-recipe">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=own-it">own-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=series-book">series-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=2020-read-books">2020-read-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=age-adult-books">age-adult-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=2000-2020-release">2000-2020-release</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2520645-my-bookish-delights?shelf=format-ebook">format-ebook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2400514188" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5754321656694381733">This was a nice wholesome Amish romance. I don&apos;t know why I love reading about the Amish community, but I always have. This one had a theme of grief and loss. I can&apos;t say that it hit me too deeply though because I didn&apos;t really connect too much with the characters. <br/><br/>It starts out at a funeral of a young man Seth and is in the perspective of his best friend and his fiancee. I kind of wish we had gotten to know Seth a bit more prior to his death so I would have felt a bit more of the loss of these </span>
  <span id="freeText5754321656694381733" style="display:none">This was a nice wholesome Amish romance. I don't know why I love reading about the Amish community, but I always have. This one had a theme of grief and loss. I can't say that it hit me too deeply though because I didn't really connect too much with the characters. <br /><br />It starts out at a funeral of a young man Seth and is in the perspective of his best friend and his fiancee. I kind of wish we had gotten to know Seth a bit more prior to his death so I would have felt a bit more of the loss of these two characters. Like most Amish centered books I read, I loved the wholesomeness of the characters and how much their families loved each other. The romance was sweet, even if a bit fast. The ending was a bit predictable.<br /><br />Kind of a middle of the road one for me, so I would really only recommend if someone already likes Amish romances.<br /><br />CAWPILE Score: 6.29 = 3 stars<br />Characters: 7<br />Atmosphere: 6<br />Writing: 6<br />Plot: 6<br />Intrigue: 5<br />Logic: 8<br />Enjoyment: 6 </span>
  <a data-text-id="5754321656694381733" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


